# CLI commands (mkdo)

Use **`mkdo`** from `/home/ken/ws/util` to install Python commands. Do not create `scripts/` dirs or `#!/usr/bin/env python3` entrypoints.

## Shared global environment (default)

All lightweight workspace CLIs live in **`~/.local/share/uv/global`** (packages) and **`~/.local/bin`** (wrappers). No per-project venv activation needed.

```bash
global_setup              # refresh all projects + commands (after clone or new project)
fish sync
sitehost deploy --dry-run
```

**`daime`** is the exception — keep its own `.venv` (GPU deps).

Wrappers in `~/.local/bin` use the **`global`** mkdo template (pinned interpreter):

```sh
exec "$HOME/.local/share/uv/global/bin/python" -m package.module "$@"
```

## Prefer `<command>` over `uv run python -m …`

```bash
# ✅ GOOD — from any directory, no venv activation
sitehost deploy --dry-run
fish sync
whip host.sitehost

# ❌ BAD — collides with /usr/bin/host (DNS lookup tool)
host sites
uv run python -m host.cli deploy
```

## Layout

- Package code under **`src/<package>/`**
- One module per command: `src/<package>/<command>.py` with `main()` and `if __name__ == "__main__"`
- Top-level CLI: `mkdo host.sitehost -d ~/.local/bin -t global` → **`sitehost`**
- Subcommands live in `cli.py` via `@cmd` — prefer one top-level command over many `mkdo package.submodule` wrappers unless a service must run standalone (e.g. long-running HTTP server as `host serve`)

## Install a command (global)

After adding a module to an existing project:

```bash
mkdo host.sitehost -d ~/.local/bin -t global
```

For a **new project**, add it to `util/global_setup.py` and run `global_setup`.

Project `pyproject.toml` should depend on **`util`** (editable path to `/home/ken/ws/util`).

## Per-project venv (optional)

For isolated dev or dependency experiments only:

```bash
cd /path/to/project
uv sync
mkdo_setup
mkdo host.sitehost -d .venv/bin
```

## New commands

```bash
mkpy mytool
# move module into src/<package>/<command>.py
mkdo <package>.<command> -d ~/.local/bin -t global
```

## Do not

- `python scripts/foo.py` or `uv run python scripts/foo.py`
- `uv run python -m <package>.<module>` for installed mkdo commands
- `[project.scripts]` entry points (use mkdo wrappers instead; tesla-fleet-mcp is legacy exception)
- `#!/usr/bin/env python3` shebangs on command modules
